Arsenal Holdings Plc (AFC) â€™s fiscal full-
year profit doubled as the London soccer team benefited from the
sales of Cesc Fabregas and Samir Nasri.  Net income rose to 29.6 million pounds ($48 million), or
475 pounds a share, in the year ended May 31, from 12.6 million
pounds, or 203 pounds, the operating company said today in a
PRNewswire statement.  Arsenal made 26 million pounds from selling players
including club captain Fabregas to Barcelona and French winger
Nasri to  Manchester City  in the fiscal year, compared with a
loss of 14.6 million in the year-earlier period.  The team had 153.6 million pounds in cash, down slightly
from the year-earlier period, and had debts of 98.9 million.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
